SSD is the minimum visible length of roadway
required for a motorist traveling at the design
speed to react and stop before reaching a
stationary object in the road (assumed to be a
vehicle entering or exiting the site). ISD is the
minimum distance required for a driver of a
stopped vehicle to view the intersecting roadway
and decide when to enter the roadway or cross it
in order to anticipate and avoid collisions.
